From 982531392de66b4352a3e63cbca5d3f98adb36e0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Hugues Clouatre <hugues@linux.com>
Date: Thu Mar 12 17:09:08 2026 -0400
Subject: fix(agents): add code-analyze MCP tools to scout and guard frontmatter

Add mcp__code-analyze__analyze_directory, mcp__code-analyze__analyze_file,
and mcp__code-analyze__analyze_symbol to the tools frontmatter in
goose-coder-scout.md and goose-coder-guard.md. Both agents reference
these tools in their instructions but were missing the frontmatter
declarations needed for Claude subagent access.

Remove mcp__aptu__review_pr from goose-coder-check.md tools frontmatter.
The CHECK agent never calls this tool; it is invoked by the orchestrator
in Phase 5 after PR creation, not by CHECK.

Fixes #349

diff --git a/config/claude/agents/goose-coder-check.md b/config/claude/agents/goose-coder-check.md
index 93b8372..f1d1c8f 100644
--- a/config/claude/agents/goose-coder-check.md
+++ b/config/claude/agents/goose-coder-check.md
@@ -2,7 +2,7 @@
 name: goose-coder-check
 description: Validates implementation matches plan requirements. Security gate and compliance checker. Receives SESSION_ID and WORKTREE via task context.
 model: haiku
-tools: ["Read", "Bash", "Glob", "Grep", "mcp__aptu__scan_security", "mcp__aptu__review_pr"]
+tools: ["Read", "Bash", "Glob", "Grep", "mcp__aptu__scan_security"]
 ---
 
